HEADWORD: Dipyridine
<hw>Di*pyr"i*dine</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>pyridine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A
polymeric form of pyridine, <chform>C10H10N2</chform>, obtained as a
colorless oil by the action of sodium on pyridine.</def>⟦br⟧
